commit.message: CI: Test on recent Erlang/OTP version

rebar.config: Add eunit to PLT

Avoid dialyzer warnings due to eunit missing from the PLT.

Separate white/blacklists for clients and peers

Allow for specifying blacklists/whitelists for TURN clients and TURN
peers separately.

Fix expiry of nonces

Don't fail to expire nonces when the ?NONCE_LIFETIME has passed.

Avoid unnecessary type conversion

The integer_to_binary/1 function is available since OTP R16B, we don't
support older versions.

Handle transport autodetection error gracefully

Don't crash if checking for a TLS connection fails.

Fixes processone/eturnal#33.

stun_test: Increase receive timeout

Don't let (esp. TLS) tests fail on slow systems.

Many thanks to Saarko for his help with tracking down the issue.

Improve TCP/TLS performance

Perform less aggressive flow control for TCP/TLS connections if no
traffic shaper is configured.

Run callbacks on protocol error events

If the caller handed over a {hook_fun, fun((event(), info()) -> ok)},
report STUN/TURN errors by calling the function with a 'protocol_error'
event() and a 'reason' element added to the info() map.

turn_sm: Avoid crash during shutdown

Catch the case where an allocation is deleted after turn_sm was
terminated during shutdown.
stun_logger: Explicitly update existing map value

stun_listener: Apply cosmetic changes

Use map syntax rather than the maps module for map updates/lookups.
Also, use consistent variable name capitalization.
